cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Meridian: a China–EU/UK trade-statistics monitor for journalists"
message: >-
  If you cite findings, methodology, or code derived from this tool,
  please cite it using the metadata below.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Hoyland
    given-names: Luke
    affiliation: "Guardian News & Media Limited"
repository-code: "https://github.com/hoyla/meridian"
abstract: >-
  Meridian ingests three customs feeds — GACC (China), Eurostat Comext
  (EU-27) and HMRC OTS (UK) — into a shared schema, cross-compares
  them, and writes deterministic Markdown briefs, spreadsheet bundles
  and LLM-drafted lead scaffolds for newsroom use. Findings are
  versioned and superseded rather than overwritten so that citation
  tokens remain stable across re-runs.
keywords:
  - journalism
  - trade-statistics
  - china
  - eurostat
  - hmrc
  - gacc
  - data-journalism
license: Apache-2.0
